    <div class="field field-name-field-ww-summary field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>With Drupal 8 on the horizon, I decided it was time to start upgrading a contributed module that I maintain called <a href="https://drupal.org/project/snippets">Code Snippets</a> to Drupal 8.</p>

<p>The module in Drupal 7 allows you to store code examples/snippets in a field. It ships with a custom field called "Snippets field" and it renders three form elements, description, source code and syntax highlighting mode (what programming language).</p>

<p>But now it's time to upgrade the module to Drupal 8.</p>

<p>In this tutorial, I'll show you how I created a "basic" custom field in Drupal 8. I won't go into detail about <a href="https://drupal.org/node/1971198">PSR-0</a>, <a href="https://drupal.org/node/1882526">annotations</a> or <a href="https://drupal.org/node/2087839">plugins</a> or this tutorial will be huge.</p>
